      <hedline>
        <hl1>Batter Up! The Battle of New York Is at Hand</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For a 6-Year-Old Boy, the Series Is but a Dream'' (letter, Oct. 18):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''For a 6-Year-Old Boy, the Series Is but a Dream'' (letter, Oct. 18):</p>
        <p>While parents in New York may be frustrated that a Subway Series is played too late for their children to see the final innings of any game, those New Yorkers who now live on the opposite coast have a different problem: we can watch every game with plenty of evening time to spare, but we miss out on the community-wide frenzy that will grip New York for the rest of October.</p>
        <p>KEITH CONRAD  La Jolla, Calif., Oct. 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
